---
intent: >
  Implement pkg-pulse from scaffolding to a working `npx pkg-pulse <package-name>`
  CLI that fetches npm registry, GitHub API, and OSV data, scores package health
  across six weighted categories, and renders a terminal report with per-signal
  breakdown and confidence indicator.
---

## Plan

### 1. Project scaffolding — TypeScript, Node 22, Vitest, bin entry

Read: `coding-playbook/foundations/conventions`, `coding-playbook/workflow/testing`, `coding-playbook/workflow/config-environment`

- [x] Initialize the project: `package.json` with `name: "pkg-pulse"`, `type: "module"`, `bin: { "pkg-pulse": "./dist/bin.js" }`, engines `>=22`, and scripts (`build`, `dev`, `test:unit`, `lint`)
- [x] Create `tsconfig.json`: target `ES2022`, module `NodeNext`, moduleResolution `NodeNext`, `outDir: "./dist"`, `rootDir: "./src"`, strict, `baseUrl: "."`, paths `@/*` -> `./src/*`. No `noEmit` — this compiles to JS for the bin entry
- [x] Create `vitest.config.ts`: environment `node`, include `src/**/*.test.ts`, path alias `@/` -> `./src`
- [x] Install dev dependencies: `typescript`, `vitest`, `@types/node`. No runtime dependencies yet — all data fetching uses Node 22 native `fetch`
- [x] Create the folder skeleton (empty `index.ts` files as placeholders): `src/bin/index.ts` (CLI entry), `src/score/index.ts` (scoring engine orchestrator), `src/fetch/index.ts` (data-fetching layer orchestrator), `src/types/index.ts` (shared types), `src/render/index.ts` (terminal output)

### 2. Type definitions — domain types for all layers

Read: `coding-playbook/workflow/type-system`, `coding-playbook/architecture/data-flow`

- [x] In `src/types/index.ts`, define and export all shared types. Key types:
  - `PackageHealth` — the top-level result: `{ name, version, score, confidence, categories: Record<CategoryName, CategoryScore>, warnings: Warning[], dataSources: string[], unavailableSignals: UnavailableSignal[] }`
  - `CategoryName` — string literal union: `"maintenance" | "security" | "supplyChain" | "license" | "community" | "quality"`
  - `CategoryScore` — `{ name: CategoryName, score: number, weight: number, label: string, details: string[] }`
  - `Warning` — `{ severity: "info" | "warning" | "critical", message: string }`
  - `UnavailableSignal` — `{ signal: string, reason: string }`
  - `NpmPackument` — shape of the npm registry packument response (relevant fields only: `name`, `dist-tags`, `time`, `maintainers`, `license`, `repository`, `versions` record with `deprecated`, `dependencies`, `hasInstallScript`, `scripts`, `_npmUser`, `dist`, `readme`, `types`/`typings`)
  - `GithubRepoData` — shape returned by the GitHub repo endpoint (relevant fields: `archived`, `pushed_at`, `open_issues_count`, `stargazers_count`, `license`, `default_branch`)
  - `GithubContributorStat` — shape from `/stats/contributors`
  - `GithubCommitActivity` — shape from `/stats/commit_activity`
  - `OsvVulnerability` — shape from OSV query response
  - `NpmDownloads` — shape from npm download-counts API
  - `FetchResult` — the aggregated raw data bag passed from the fetch layer to the scoring engine: `{ packument, downloads, githubRepo, githubContributors, githubCommitActivity, vulnerabilities }` where each field is `T | null` (null = unavailable)
  - `CategoryWeights` — `Record<CategoryName, number>` with the six weights from the spec
- [x] Use `as const satisfies` for the `CATEGORY_WEIGHTS` constant object and the `LICENSE_TIERS` lookup table, co-located in a `src/types/constants.ts` file

### 3. Data-fetching layer — npm registry client

Read: `coding-playbook/architecture/patterns`, `coding-playbook/services/error-handling`

- [x] Create `src/fetch/index.ts` as the orchestrator: it takes `{ packageName: string, githubToken?: string }` and returns `Promise<FetchResult>`. It fetches the packument first (sequential — needed for repo URL and version), then fans out all other fetches in parallel using `Promise.allSettled`. Each settled result maps to `T | null` in `FetchResult`. The orchestrator has step-by-step inline comments narrating the pipeline
- [x] Create `src/fetch/fetchPackument/index.ts` — fetches `https://registry.npmjs.org/<encodedName>` (handle scoped package URL encoding), returns typed `NpmPackument`. Throws on 404 (package not found) — this is the only hard failure. Throws on network error
- [x] Create `src/fetch/fetchDownloads/index.ts` — fetches last-week and last-month download counts from the npm API (`https://api.npmjs.org/downloads/point/last-week/<name>` and `last-month`), returns `NpmDownloads`
- [x] Create `src/fetch/extractRepoUrl/index.ts` — pure function that extracts a GitHub owner/repo pair from the packument's `repository` field (handles `github:user/repo`, full HTTPS URLs, git+ssh URLs, shorthand). Returns `{ owner, repo, directory?: string } | null`

### 4. Data-fetching layer — GitHub and OSV clients

Read: `coding-playbook/architecture/patterns`, `coding-playbook/services/error-handling`

- [x] Create `src/fetch/fetchGithubRepo/index.ts` — fetches `https://api.github.com/repos/:owner/:repo`, injects `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header when `githubToken` is present, returns typed `GithubRepoData | null`. Returns `null` on 403 (rate limited) or 404. Handles the 202 retry pattern for stats endpoints
- [x] Create `src/fetch/fetchGithubContributors/index.ts` — fetches `/repos/:owner/:repo/stats/contributors`, handles 202 retry (up to 3 attempts with 1s delay), returns `GithubContributorStat[] | null`
- [x] Create `src/fetch/fetchGithubCommitActivity/index.ts` — fetches `/repos/:owner/:repo/stats/commit_activity`, handles 202 retry, returns `GithubCommitActivity[] | null`
- [x] Create `src/fetch/fetchVulnerabilities/index.ts` — POSTs to `https://api.osv.dev/v1/query` with `{ package: { name, ecosystem: "npm" }, version }` for the target package, returns `OsvVulnerability[]`. Also supports batch queries via `https://api.osv.dev/v1/querybatch` for dependency CVE checking
- [x] Create `src/fetch/fetchDeprecatedDeps/index.ts` — takes the direct dependency list from the packument, fetches each dependency's packument in parallel (using `Promise.allSettled`), returns a list of `{ name: string, deprecated: string }` for any that have a `deprecated` field on their latest version

### 5. Scoring engine — category scorers with handler array dispatch

Read: `coding-playbook/architecture/patterns`, `coding-playbook/workflow/type-system`, `coding-playbook/foundations/conventions`

- [x] Create `src/score/index.ts` as the scoring orchestrator: takes `FetchResult` and returns `PackageHealth`. Uses the handler array dispatch pattern — imports all six category scorers, iterates them in sequence, each returns a `CategoryScore | null` (null if required data is unavailable). After all handlers run, computes the weighted aggregate using only non-null categories (re-normalizing weights to available signals). Computes `confidence` as the percentage of total weight backed by data. Collects warnings from all scorers. Inline comments narrate each step
- [x] Create `src/score/scoreMaintenance/index.ts` — scores publish recency (decay curve from spec), bus factor (from GitHub contributor stats), deprecation status, archived status, and the "finished project" exception. Input: `FetchResult`. Returns `CategoryScore` with detail strings
- [x] Create `src/score/scoreSecurity/index.ts` — scores current-version CVEs weighted by severity (CRITICAL=0 override, HIGH/MODERATE/LOW penalties), plus dependency CVE exposure from the batch OSV query. Input: `FetchResult`
- [x] Create `src/score/scoreSupplyChain/index.ts` — scores install script presence (escalated if new in current version), maintainer changes between recent versions, publish frequency anomalies, provenance/Sigstore attestation. Input: `FetchResult`
- [x] Create `src/score/scoreLicense/index.ts` — maps license to five-tier SPDX risk model using the `LICENSE_TIERS` lookup, normalizes non-standard strings, handles compound SPDX expressions (OR = least restrictive, AND = most restrictive), flags npm/GitHub license mismatch. Input: `FetchResult`
- [x] Create `src/score/scoreCommunity/index.ts` — scores download trend (last-week vs last-month ratio), GitHub stars, contributor diversity. Trend weighted more heavily than raw count. Input: `FetchResult`
- [x] Create `src/score/scoreQuality/index.ts` — scores README presence and length, TypeScript type declarations (bundled or `@types/`), test script presence, GitHub community health percentage. Input: `FetchResult`

